MEMBERS of the Port Elizabeth Flying Squad acting
on intelligence, arrested a man for trying to evade arrest and was
found with drugs. They spotted a white VW Polo in Whyteleaf Drive in
Algoa Park. It's alleged as the flying squad attempted to stop
the vehicle, the driver drove through a red robot while trying to escape. The suspect then collided into another vehicle, the
VW Polo continued crashing into other vehicles while trying to escape. "In an attempt to stop him, a shot was fired
at the tyre of the vehicle. The driver lost control and collided with a traffic
light. On searching the vehicle, 296 tik pipes, 66 mandrax tablets, 1 packet of
tik and an undisclosed amount of money was seized," Captain Sandra Janse
van Rensburg said. Van Rensburg said the suspect was jailed on charges
of attempted murder, dealing in drugs and reckless and negligent driving. The vehicle was also confiscated, and the suspect is
expected to appear in court on Monday. The Cluster Commander for Mount Road, Maj Gen
Thembisile Patekile has applauded the Port Elizabeth Flying Squad for their
excellent arrest and immediate response to the information received.